{"title_page": "Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?", "text_new": "{{short description|American animated television series}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?\n| image                    = File:Scooby-doo-guess-who.jpg\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = Promotional logo\n| show_name_2              = \n| genre                    = [[Comedy]]<br>[[Mystery film|Mystery]]\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Scooby-Doo, Where Are You!]]''<br>''[[The New Scooby-Doo Movies]]''|[[Joe Ruby]] and [[Ken Spears]]}}\n| director                 = \n| voices                   = {{unbulleted list|[[Frank Welker]]|[[Grey DeLisle|Grey Griffin]]|[[Matthew Lillard]]|[[Kate Micucci]]}}\n| opentheme                = \"Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?\" performed by [[Vivek Maddala]] and David Poe\n| composer                 = Steven Morrell<br>[[Adam Berry]]\n| country                  = United States\n| language                 = English\n| channel                  = [[Cartoon Network]]<br>[[Boomerang (TV network)#Mobile app/subscription service|Boomerang SVOD]]\n| executive_producer       = {{unbulleted list|Vishnu Athreya and Diana Theobald <small>(for [[Boomerang (TV network)|Boomerang]])</small>|Jay Bastian|[[Sam Register]]}}\n| producer                 = [[Chris Bailey (animator)|Chris Bailey]]\n| editor                   = \n| company                  = [[Warner Bros. Animation]]<br>[[Hanna-Barbera|Hanna-Barbera Cartoons]]<br> Yeson Entertainment \n(animation service)<br>\n| distributor              = [[Warner Bros. Television Distribution]]\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_episodes             = 13\n| list_episodes            = #Episode list\n| runtime                  = 22 minutes\n| picture_format           = 1080i HDTV\n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = \n| first_aired              = {{Start date|2019|06|27}}\n| last_aired               = present\n| preceded_by              = ''[[Be Cool, Scooby-Doo!]]'' <small>(2015\u201318)</small>\n| related                  = \n| website                  = https://watch.boomerang.com/shows/guess-who-franchise\n| website_title            = Watch on Boomerang\n| production_website       = \n| production_website_title = \n}}\n'''''Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?''''' is an American animated television series produced by [[Warner Bros. Animation]] for [[Cartoon Network]] and [[Boomerang (TV network)|Boomerang]]. It is the thirteenth installment produced in the ''[[Scooby-Doo]]'' franchise. The series is produced by [[Chris Bailey (animator)|Chris Bailey]].\n\nThe show premiered on the [[Boomerang (TV network)#Mobile app/subscription service|Boomerang streaming service and app]] on June 27, 2019.<ref name=animationmagazine2>{{cite news|date=2018-05-23|title=Boomerang Unveils New SCOOBY-DOO AND GUESS WHO? & YABBA-DABBA DINOSAURS! Series|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/bwwtv/article/Boomerang-Unveils-New-SCOOBY-DOO-AND-GUESS-WHO-YABBA-DABBA-DINOSAURS-Series-20180523|work=Broadway World}}</ref> It also premiered on [[Cartoon Network]] on July 8, 2019. The show is rated TV-PG, making this the first ''Scooby-Doo'' series to carry that rating.\n\n==Premise==\n''Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?'' focuses on the Mystery Inc. gang as they solve mysteries while also encountering many memorable celebrities, similar in ''[[The New Scooby-Doo Movies]]''. Guest stars that have appeared include [[Chris Paul]], [[Sia (musician)|Sia]], [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]], [[Ricky Gervais]], [[Kenan Thompson]], [[Wanda Sykes]], [[Bill Nye]], [[Neil deGrasse Tyson]] and [[Mark Hamill]], along with characters such as [[Steve Urkel]], [[Batman]], [[Sherlock Holmes]], [[Flash (Barry Allen)|Flash]], [[Wonder Woman]], [[Magilla Gorilla]] and Mr. Peebles, and [[The Funky Phantom]].\n\nUnlike in The New Scooby-Doo Movies, the show is intended for a 30-minute block on TV instead of a 60-minute block and includes somewhat of a parody of the guest stars.\n\nThe tone of the show is comedic and does not include an overarching plot. The animation style is new to the Scooby-Doo franchise but is designed to look similar to how cartoons were drawn in the 1960s and 1970s.\n\n==Voice cast==\n{{main|List of Scooby-Doo characters}}\n\n===Main cast===\n* [[Frank Welker]] - [[Fred Jones (Scooby-Doo)|Fred Jones]], [[Scooby-Doo (character)|Scooby-Doo]]\n* [[Grey DeLisle|Grey Griffin]] - [[Daphne Blake]]\n* [[Matthew Lillard]] - [[Shaggy Rogers|Norville \"Shaggy\" Rogers]]\n* [[Kate Micucci]] - [[Velma Dinkley]]\n\n===Guest stars===\n* [[Kevin Conroy]] - [[Batman|Bruce Wayne / Batman]] (in \"What a Night, For a Dark Knight!\")<ref name=Insta>{{cite news|date=2018-05-25|title=Matthew Lillard on Instagram|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BWvgDwpj5DY|work=Instagram }}</ref>\n* [[Ian James Corlett]] - [[Sherlock Holmes]] (in \"Elementary, My Dear Shaggy!\")<ref name=FutonCritic/>\n* [[John DiMaggio]] - [[Abraham Lincoln]] (in \"A Mystery Solving Gang Divided\")<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/entertainment/herocomplex/la-et-hc-scooby-doo-guess-who-trailer-20190620-story.html|title=New \u2018Scooby Doo\u2019 trailer turns Chris Paul, Sia and Wonder Woman into cartoons|date=June 20, 2019|website=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\n* [[Jim Gaffigan]] - Himself (in \"The Fastest Food Fiend!\")<ref name=FutonCritic/>\n* [[Ricky Gervais]] - Himself (in \"Ollie Ollie In-Come Free!\")\n<!--* [[Whoopi Goldberg]] - Herself<ref>https://www.tvinsider.com/788081/scooby-doo-and-guess-who-boomerang-premiere/</ref> (in \"The Nightmare Ghost of Psychic U!\")>-->\n<!--* [[Halsey (singer)|Halsey]] - Herself>-->\n* [[Mark Hamill]] - [[Joker (character)|The Joker]] (in \"What a Night, For a Dark Knight!\"), Himself\n* [[Rachel Kimsey]] - [[Wonder Woman]] (in \"The Scooby of a Thousand Faces!\")<ref name=FutonCritic>{{Cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/news/2019/06/20/jinkies-new-series-scooby-doo-and-guess-who-to-world-premiere-on-boomerang-583304/20190620boomerang01/|title=Breaking News - Jinkies! New Series \"Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?\" to World Premiere on Boomerang &#124; TheFutonCritic.com|website=www.thefutoncritic.com}}</ref>\n<!--* [[Bill Nye]] - Himself>-->\n* [[Chris Paul]] - Himself (in \"Revenge of the Swamp Monster!\")\n* [[Penn & Teller]] - Themselves (in \"The Cursed Cabinet of Professor Madds Markson!\")<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://scoobysnax1.weebly.com/1/post/2018/07/a-first-look-at-scooby-doo-and-guess-who.html|title=A First Look at Scooby-Doo and Guess Who?|website=ScoobySnax.com}}</ref>\n* [[Sia (musician)|Sia]] - Herself (in \"Now You Sia, Now You Don't!\")\n* [[Wanda Sykes]] - Herself (in \"Peebles' Pet Shop of Terrible Terrors!\")<ref name=FutonCritic/>\n* [[Kenan Thompson]] - Himself (in \"Quit Clowning!\")\n<!--* [[Neil deGrasse Tyson]] - Himself>-->\n* [[Steven Weber]] - [[Alfred Pennyworth]] (in \"What a Night, For a Dark Knight!\")\n* [[Jaleel White]] - [[Steve Urkel]], Urkel-Bot (in \"When Urkel-Bots Go Bad!\")\n* [[\"Weird Al\" Yankovic]] - Himself (in \"Attack of the Weird Al-Osaurus!\")<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ign.com/articles/2019/06/20/scooby-doo-and-guess-who-trailer-premiere-date-ricky-gervais-weird-al-kevin-conroy|title=Scooby-Doo and Guess Who Reveals First Trailer, Premiere Date and Celebrity Cameos - IGN|via=www.ign.com}}</ref>\n<!--* TBA - [[Flash (Barry Allen)|The Flash]]<ref name=animationmagazine2/>-->\n* [[George Takei]] - Himself\n\n==Episodes==\n=== Series overview ===\n\n{{Series overview\n| color1           = #000070\n| link1            = #Season 1 (2019)\n| episodes1        = 13\n| start1           = {{Start date|2019|06|27}}\n| end1             = {{Start date|2019|9|19}}\n\n| color2           = #000070\n| link2            = #Season 2 (2020)\n| episodes2        = 13\n| start2           = {{N/A|TBA}}\n| end2             = {{N/A|TBA}}\n}}\n\n=== Season 1 (2019) ===\n{{Episode table |background=#000070 |overall=5 |season=5 |title=28 |aux1=20 |director=10 |writer=36 |airdate=15 |aux1T=Guest star(s) |episodes=\n\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=1\n|EpisodeNumber2=1\n|Title=Revenge of the Swamp Monster!\n|DirectedBy=Jae Kim\n|WrittenBy=Michael Ryan\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|06|27}}\n|Aux1=[[Chris Paul]]\n|ShortSummary=After Mystery Inc. solves the mystery of the Bee Man of [[Alcatraz Island|Alcatraz]], they are flown to [[Florida]] where Shaggy is to [[Caddie|caddy]] for [[Houston Rockets]] basketball player and bowling fan Chris Paul at a charity golf event to raise money for a struggling arts school, which is on the brink of going bankrupt because of a [[swamp monster]] causing trouble for the tournament.\n* '''Villain''': Swamp Monster/The Caddy\n|LineColor=000070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=2\n|EpisodeNumber2=2\n|Title=A Mystery Solving Gang Divided\n|DirectedBy=Frank Paur\n|WrittenBy=Mark Hoffmeier\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|7|2}}\n|Aux1=[[Abraham Lincoln]]<!--While the Funky Phantom crew do play a significant role, only Lincoln is credited as the special guest star.-->\n|ShortSummary=Mystery Inc. receives a call from [[Chambersburg, Pennsylvania]], a battlefield nearby [[Gettysburg, Pennsylvania]], to solve the mystery of ghost zombie [[American civil war|Civil War]] soldiers, only to bump into ''[[The Funky Phantom]]'' crew. Although both mystery solving teams get into subsequent conflicts until the spirit of Abraham Lincoln suggests they should work together and save the mystery for last once and for all.\n* '''Villain''': Ghost Sergeant/Jebb\n|LineColor=000070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=3\n|EpisodeNumber2=3\n|Title=Peebles' Pet Shop of Terrible Terrors!\n|DirectedBy=Mike Milo\n|WrittenBy=Caroline Farah\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|7|11}}\n|Aux1=[[Wanda Sykes]]\n|ShortSummary=An egg that was delivered to Peebles' Pet Supply Mega-Store hatches into a fish monster and makes off with Mr. Peebles. Later, Scooby and the gang arrive at the crime scene and rescue Mr. Peebles' intern, Wanda Sykes, who is helping save a bunch of animals up for adoption in a pet supply store. Now, our heroes and Wanda must not only save the store and the animals, but their own lives. As Mystery Inc. and Wanda work to solve the mystery, they also have an encounter with [[Magilla Gorilla]].\n* '''Villain''': Fish Monster/Mr. Peebles\n|LineColor=000070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=4\n|EpisodeNumber2=4\n|Title=Elementary, My Dear Shaggy!\n|DirectedBy=Mike Milo\n|WrittenBy=Michael Ryan\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|7|18}}\n|Aux1=[[Sherlock Holmes]]\n|ShortSummary=When Scooby and the gang are taking a tour of [[London]], they run afoul of horrible screaming skulls of English legend! They team up with an eccentric man who claims to be none other than Sherlock Holmes. Also, during this time, he refers to Velma as [[Dr. Watson]] and Shaggy as Mrs. Hudson.\n* '''Villains''': Screaming Skulls/[[Yeomen Warders|Beefeater]] and Security Guard\n|LineColor=000070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=5\n|EpisodeNumber2=5\n|Title=Ollie Ollie In-Come Free!\n|DirectedBy=Mike Milo\n|WrittenBy=Mike Ryan\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|7|25}}\n|Aux1=[[Ricky Gervais]]\n|ShortSummary=In London, Mystery Inc. visits Ricky Gervais when a cat [[Mummy (monster)|mummy]] comes unannounced from his door with a connection with the Egyptian goddess [[Bastet|Bast]]. At this rate, the gang agrees to prevent the statue of Bast from falling into the wrong hands.\n* '''Villain''': Cat Mummy/Antique Dealer\n|LineColor=000070\n}}\n{{Episode list\n|EpisodeNumber=6\n|EpisodeNumber2=6\n|Title=The Scooby of a Thousand Faces!\n|DirectedBy=Gavin Dell\n|WrittenBy=Caroline Farah\n|OriginalAirDate={{Start date|2019|8|1}}\n|Aux1=[[Wonder Woman]]\n|ShortSummary=While on vacation in [[Greece]], Mystery Inc. gets caught in a one-on-one scrimmage between a [[Minotaur]] and Wonder Woman. Although Scooby-Doo takes a liking to Wonder Woman, Daphne and Velma are the only ones elected to assist Wonder Woman